		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">6.205</ph> Set-asides for HUBZone small business concerns.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d372e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d379e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            To fulfill the statutory requirements relating to the HUBZone Act of1997 (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.631</xref> note), contracting officers in participating agencies (see <xref href="FAR-i1099558.dita#i1099558"
                        base="i1099558"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1302</xref>) may set aside solicitations to allow only qualified HUBZone small business concerns to compete (see <xref href="FAR-i1099604.dita#i1099604"
                        base="i1099604"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1305</xref>).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d379e35" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            No separate justification or determination and findings is required under this part to set aside a contract action for qualified HUBZone small business concerns.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
